Small trick for rotating arrays:
i = ith iteration
D = number of elements to rotate
N = size of array

To handle large D values, before rotating use-
if(D>N)
D %= N;

For left rotate-
arr[i] = arr[(i+D)%N]

For right rotate-
arr[i] = arr[(i+N-D)%N]

